emes. The company also offers housing loans, vehicle and car loans, topup loans, education loans, gold loans, personal loans, salary gain schemes, green financing schemes, rooftop solar panel loans, and adhaar loans, as well as loans against properties and deposits; working capital, term, project, infrastructure, export, and bill financing services; lines of credit; commercial lease rental services; accounts takeover services; non-fund based services; micro, small, and medium enterprise loans; and agriculture loans and other services. In addition, it provides digital banking and lending services, and government schemes; debit and credit cards; documentary credits and collections, import and export financing, guarantees, travel related forex, non-resident Indian services, capital account transactions, remittance schemes, and risk management services; and remittance facilities, as well as hedges exchange risk. Bank of Maharashtra was incorporated in 1935 and is headquartered in Pune, India."}}